This library is a Swift port of the DSP layer of the Phonicbloom BSAFE
(Gecho / MMXX T-APE) ESP32 firmware. The original C/C++ source is
available from Phonicbloom under its own terms; see:
    https://github.com/phonicbloom/gecho

The following BSafeEngine files are direct ports (function-for-function
translations preserving overflow semantics and constants) of the noted
firmware source files:

    Sources/BSafeEngine/BytebeatSongs.swift   <- main/bytebeat_songs.inc
    Sources/BSafeEngine/BytebeatEngine.swift  <- main/dsp/Bytebeat.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/EchoBuffer.swift      <- main/dsp/Bytebeat.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/StereoMixer.swift     <- main/dsp/Bytebeat.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/Arpeggiator.swift     <- main/dsp/Bytebeat.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/StepSequencer.swift   <- main/dsp/Bytebeat.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/SineWavesEngine.swift <- main/dsp/SineWaves.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/Wavetables.swift      <- main/dsp/SineWaves.cpp
    Sources/BSafeEngine/MiniPiano.swift       <- main/dsp/SineWaves.h

The eight built-in bytebeat formulas descend from the "bytebeat"
tradition originated by Ville-Matias Heikkila (Viznut). See:
    https://countercomplex.blogspot.com/2011/10/algorithmic-symphonies-from-one-line-of.html

